{
  "texts": [
    "These graphs are updated using a GGNN.",
    "An external spatial memory is constructed to aggregate information from across the graphs as they are updated, using a neural network with an attention mechanism.",
    "The final state of the spatial memory is used to perform the final task.",
    "Modern graph neural network architecturesIn recent years, the limits of message passing GNNs have become increasingly evident, from their tendency to oversmooth the input features as the depth of the network increases [104] to their unsatisfactory performance in heterophilic settings [105], i.e.",
    "when neighbouring nodes in the input graphs are dissimilar."
  ]
}